# Template for secrets and machine-specific overrides. Committed.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is gitignored) and fill in the keys.
# Anything in `.env.local` overrides the same variable in `.env`.
#
# Loading: `python -m mathagent` and the `mathagent` console script auto-load
# .env and .env.local on startup. You do NOT need to source the files
# manually for the normal REPL flow. The README's manual-source snippet is
# only for ad-hoc commands that do not go through the entry point.

# The default TRACING_BACKEND in `.env` is `both`, so the agent will try to
# send traces to LangSmith AND LangFuse. Filling only one set of keys is
# fine: the other backend logs one "disabled" line at startup and no-ops.

# ---- LangSmith ----
# Used when LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2 is true (default) and TRACING_BACKEND is
# `langsmith` or `both`.
# Get a key at https://smith.langchain.com/ -> Settings -> API Keys -> Create.
LANGCHAIN_API_KEY=

# ---- LangFuse ----
# Used when TRACING_BACKEND is `langfuse` or `both` (the default).
# Sign up at https://cloud.langfuse.com/ (or self-host), then in your project
# go to Settings -> API Keys -> Create new API keys.
LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY=
LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=
